    "subtopic": "inverse-matrix",
    "level": "A-Level",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "type": "multiple-choice",
    "content": {
      "text": "เมทริกซ์ผกผันของ $A = \\begin{pmatrix} 2 & 1 \\\\ 5 & 3 \\end{pmatrix}$ คือข้อใด",
      "choices": {
        "a": "$\\begin{pmatrix} 3 & -1 \\\\ -5 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$",
        "b": "$\\begin{pmatrix} 3 & 1 \\\\ 5 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$",
        "c": "$\\begin{pmatrix} 2 & -1 \\\\ -5 & 3 \\end{pmatrix}$",
        "d": "$\\begin{pmatrix} -3 & 1 \\\\ 5 & -2 \\end{pmatrix}$",
        "e": "$\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & -1 \\\\ -5 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$"
      }
    },
    "answer": "a",
    "hint": "$A^{-1} = \\dfrac{1}{\\det(A)}\\begin{pmatrix} d & -b \\\\ -c & a \\end{pmatrix}$",
    "solution": {
      "steps": [
        "$\\det(A) = 2 \\cdot 3 - 1 \\cdot 5 = 6 - 5 = 1$",
        "$A^{-1} = \\dfrac{1}{1}\\begin{pmatrix} 3 & -1 \\\\ -5 & 2 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 3 & -1 \\\\ -5 & 2 \\end{pmatrix}$"
      ],
      "keyFormula": "$A^{-1} = \\dfrac{1}{ad-bc}\\begin{pmatrix} d & -b \\\\ -c & a \\end{pmatrix}$"
    },
    "tags": ["inverse-matrix"],
    "source": "A-Level 2565"
  }
]
